DECEMBER 16, 1942

Will Bingham v. The State. No. 22340. Delivered December 16, 1942.

The opinion states the case.

Aubrey Davee, of Brady, for appellant. Spurgeon E. Bell, State’s Attorney, of Austin, for the State. GRAVES, Judge.

Upon a trial before a jury appellant was fined $150.00 for violation of the local option liquor law of McCulloch County.

There are no bills of exceptions in the record, and the statement of facts reflect a sale of whisky in a dry area.

All proceedings appear to be regular, and the judgment is affirmed.
